<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="103" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d103">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Young</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tegucigalpa</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-27"><hi rend="italic">December 27,
                                    1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Made demand upon this Government Renton matter, and have had one
                            conference with the President, and satisfied that they are trying to
                            gain time. They urge reasonable delay. Recent demand has been made by
                            British charge d’affaires that Dawe, one of the murderers, shall be
                            liberated, claiming preliminary examination was a trial; it was
                            preliminary investigation only. I have another meeting Saturday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Young.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>